Hindustan Copper Ltd. , Indiaâ€™s
largest miner of the ore, filed a prospectus with the market
regulator to sell 183.9 million shares, according to an e-mailed
statement from the company.  The company and the Indian government will sell 92.5
million shares each. About 1 million shares will be reserved for
eligible employees, the statement said.  Institutional buyers will be able to buy up to 50 percent
of the shares in the sale, which will be conducted through a
book-building process, the statement said.  ICICI Securities Ltd., Enam Securities Private Ltd., Kotak
Mahindra Capital Co., SBI Capital Markets Ltd. and UBS
Securities India Private Ltd. will manage the sale.  To contact the reporter on this story:
